It is not possible to measure either V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{L} \)
\end_inset 

 or V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{r} \)
\end_inset 

 directly.
 The only voltage associated with the inductor that can be measured experimental
ly is the voltage across the inductor V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{ind} \)
\end_inset 

 which is the vector sum of V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{L} \)
\end_inset 

 and V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{r} \)
\end_inset 

.
\layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V_{ind}^{2}=V_{L}^{2}+V_{r}^{2}\]

\end_inset 


\layout Standard

The voltages V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{L} \)
\end_inset 

 and V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{r} \)
\end_inset 

 can be expressed in terms of the current I as
\layout Standard
\align center 

\begin_inset Formula \( V_{L}=I\omega L \)
\end_inset 

 
\layout Standard
\align center 

\begin_inset Formula \( V_{r}=Ir \)
\end_inset 


\layout Standard

If the above expressions for 
\begin_inset Formula \( V_{ind}^{2} \)
\end_inset 

, V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{L} \)
\end_inset 

, and V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{r} \)
\end_inset 

 are combined, and the current I is eliminated it can be shown that
\layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V_{L}=V_{ind}\frac{\omega L}{\sqrt{(\omega L)^{2}+r^{2}}}\]

\end_inset 


\layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V_{r}=V_{ind}\frac{r}{\sqrt{(\omega L)^{2}+r^{2}}}\]

\end_inset 


\layout Standard

Assuming that 
\begin_inset Formula \( \omega  \)
\end_inset 

, L, and r are known, V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{L} \)
\end_inset 

 and V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{r} \)
\end_inset 

 can be determined from the two expressions above if V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{ind} \)
\end_inset 

 is measured.
 These values of V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{L} \)
\end_inset 

 and V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{r} \)
\end_inset 

 combined with measured values of V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{C} \)
\end_inset 

 and V
\begin_inset Formula \( _{R} \)
\end_inset 

 can be used in the expression for V to verify the relationship between
 these quantities and the measured generator voltage V.
\layout Standard


